<br>
Anything that takes a player's control away in the game is a BAD thing. Anything that gives one group what amounts to an overwhelming advantage every time is a BAD thing. It doesn't take any skill at all to AE mez a group and everyone knows this. The only time ANYONE likes this is when they get to do it to someone else. Then it's FUN, but any other time it sucks. This in itself is indicative of a problem. Hell, keep single target mez as is, but then again it takes skill to target the biggest potential problem character in an opposing group and mez him rather than just pressing the WIN button we know as AE mez.<br>
<br>
As mez stands now it's a death sentence for the most part. I don't think anyone (except Wizards and Runemasters) would advocate Wizards and Runemasters getting a targetable instacast AE DD spell that does about 1000 rps to any enemy in the radius, yet in many cases that's exactly what mez does.<br>
<br>
The cries from the mezzers are loud right now, mostly consisting of &quot;Oh great, with mez having a counter now the group with the most people will tend to win&quot;. I mean, a statement like that oughta raise some kind of a warning flag.<br>
<br>
Bottom line is it's not fun for anyone to have their group picked apart 1 by 1 while mezzed. This is a good change for the game, especially for tanks, who BTW really need a hand in RvR. There's a respec incoming, so I fail to see what the big deal is. Granted, the mez tactic should NEVER have been put in the game in the 1st place, but if it's something as universally hated as mez you'd have to be a little slow to never expect it to change.<br>
<br>
I expect a lot of these types of changes down the road, including changes to but not limited to: PBT stacking, Pet LOS abuse, Stealth &amp; one shotting. Don't be surprised if these abilities change eventually. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#5F9EA0>- </font><a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bforgottentruthforeignlegion>Forgotten Truth Foreign Legion</a><font color=#5F9EA0> - </font><a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral>General</a> <font color=#5F9EA0> - </font><a href="http://www.forgottentruth.com">Home</a><font color=#5F9EA0> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.8.5.4<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  